tap
---
test anything protocol for c

tap.h contains functions for writing tests that respect the
Test Anything Protocol (https://testanything.org/). The API
is mainly inspired from the library written by Nik Clayton,
but differs in that is much smaller and simpler.

Requirements
------------
- a c89 compatible compiler

Install
-------
tap.h is a single header library. Place it wherever you
want: in your project directory, in your include path...

use the `install' program to copy it to a convenient
location, i.e `/usr/local/include':

> install -m 644 tap.h /usr/local/include

